title: Indiana Firm Recalls Corn Chowder Soup Products That May Contain Foreign Materials
summary: WASHINGTON, July 13, 2012 - Morgan Foods, Inc., an Austin, Ind. establishment, is recalling approximately 94,850 pounds of corn chowder soup products that may contain foreign materials, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The products subject to recall...
